[Student "S"]
{[show S]

The bidding has been as shown. It is your bid. What do you say? [BID 1NT]



A 1NT overcall is almost the same as a 1NT opening. The range is increased to 15-18, but the main difference is that you <b>must</b> have the opponent's suit adequately stopped. Here you certainly have the stopper so you bid 1NT. Partner responds 2\H. What do you bid next? [BID pass]

[show NS]



And the responses are the same also. Partner's 2\H bid is a signoff bid, often called a "drop dead" bid. So even though you really like the \Hs you pass. }


